    "content_hash": "8e6feaef74c7b7e9",
    "department": "Business",
    "description": "A little about us\n\n - Redefining graphic design: Kittl is transforming how creators work with an intuitive platform that stands as a modern, competitive alternative to traditional design tools: Build the new Adobe of tomorrow\n\n - Rapid growth: Millions of users within just two years of launch\n\n - Diverse team: 120+ team members representing 30+ different countries\n\n - Truly product-led company: Engineers, Product managers and designers are at the core of Kittl - shaping an engineering driven working culture\n\n - Strong funding: Raised over $45M from world-renowned investors who have also backed companies like Slack, Dropbox, and Figma\n\nLearn more: www.kittl.com/career http://www.kittl.com/career\n\nYour role at Kittl\n\nAs our Talent Acquisition Partner, you will own end-to-end recruitment across business and tech - from the first sourcing touch to offer and close.\n\nWe are looking for a junior to mid-level TA Partner based in Berlin (hybrid) who sources proactively, thinks strategically about pipelines, and genuinely believes that putting the right person in the right opportunity changes everything. You will be the single owner of TA at Kittl, partnering directly with hiring managers across the company.\n\nBeyond recruiting, you’ll have real room to shape how Kittl shows up externally - through employer branding, community, and how we build culture as we grow.\n\nWhat you'll do\n\n - Own the full recruitment lifecycle: Lead hiring across business and tech roles - briefing, sourcing, screening, coordinating, and closing\n\n - Source proactively: Go beyond job postings and inbound applications; find strong candidates before they're on anyone else's radar\n\n - Partner with hiring managers: Work closely with leads across product, engineering, and business - manage expectations, communicate clearly, and push back when needed\n\n - Drive a standout candidate experience: Make every touchpoint count, from first outreach to final decision\n\n - Leverage AI and automation: Implement and experiment with AI-driven sourcing, candidate engagement tools, and process automations to make hiring faster and smarter\n\n - Shape employer branding and community: Help tell Kittl’s\n   story externally, support events, and build a culture people want to be part of\n\nWhat you’ll need\n\n - Experience: At least 2 years in Talent Acquisition, ideally with both business and tech roles in your portfolio\n\n - Sourcing mindset: You don't wait for applications - you go find people, and you're good at it\n\n - Ownership and high drive: You take accountability for outcomes, operate independently, and proactively push work forward without being asked\n\n - Stakeholder partnership: You communicate well, manage expectations, and build trust with demanding hiring managers\n\n - Adaptability: You thrive in fast-moving environments; startup or scale-up experience is a plus, especially if you were the only recruiter or close to it\n\n - Tech curiosity: You’re excited to explore AI, automations, and other tools to innovate hiring processes\n\nInterview process\n\n - Recruiter interview (30 min)\n\n - Interview with People Lead (30 min)\n\n - On-site interview (60 min)\n\n - Bar raiser interview with CEO (45 min)\n\nWe are looking for someone\n\n - Exceptionally driven to drive impact and challenge the status quo\n\n - Who takes extreme ownership \u0026 gets things done\n\n - Who goes above and beyond in their role\n\n - Who is deeply passionate about what they do\n\nBenefits\n\n - Maximise your impact: No matter if you’re leading a team or you stand out by your domain expertise - all we care about is supporting you to maximise your own impact\n\n - Hackathons: Our quarterly hackathons provide an environment to experiment with new concepts, push boundaries, and potentially deliver the next big thing.\n\n - Kittl Week: Each year, our global team gathers together for a whole week, to work, celebrate, get inspired, and have fun\n\n - Flexible working hours: Our core hours are 11am–5pm CET, leaving the rest of your schedule flexible to fit your style\n\n - Remote work: Work up to 50 days (10 weeks) fully remote per year from anywhere in the world, as long as you maintain our core hours\n\n - Learning \u0026 development: Our L\u0026D budget supports your professional growth\n\n - Mobility benefit: We fully cover your monthly BVG public transport ticket\n\n - Health and fitness: Urban Sports Club membership discount\n\n - Vacation: Up to 30 vacation days per year\n\n#li-hybrid\n\n🌈 At Kittl, we embrace diversity and value every team member's unique background, identity, and experience. We're all about respect, honesty, and inclusivity. Together, we create a safe and supportive work environment where everyone thrives. Join us on this exciting journey of making our company and product even better!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
